Hi Everyone,

I&#39;ve been using jUnit with great success.  However, Keith&#39;s recent comment
brings up a question that&#39;s been on my mind for awhile:

&gt; Date: Fri, 5 Jan 2001 15:02:18 -0800
&gt; From: Keith Ray &lt;keith.ray@...&gt;

&gt; What you are doing sounds like acceptance testing. Unit testing with JUnit
&gt; is intended to QUICKLY show that all tests pass while you are refactoring,
&gt; or that only one test fails when you are writing test-first code.
&gt; 
&gt; Acceptance testing usually tests that the application satisfies the user&#39;s
&gt; Stories... failures are allowed (and expected) for un-implemented stories.
&gt; Kent Beck describes the results of Acceptance testing to be a number like
&gt; &quot;89% of tests pass&quot;.

It&#39;s clear that jUnit isn&#39;t complete support for XP-ish functional testing.
That requires something that can track pass rates over time, make sure
previously-passing tests don&#39;t start failing, maybe print some reports for
the Customer to review...

So what tools are people using to support functional testing?

Cheers,
.T.

Todd Jonker
ZEFER Pittsburgh


